# Import Organization - Raj's Strict Order

**Follow Raj's precise import ordering for clean, maintainable code.**

## ✅ Raj's Import Order:
```typescript
// 1. 'use client' directive first (if needed)
'use client';

// 2. External libraries (React, Next.js, etc.)
import { useAuthActions } from '@convex-dev/auth/react';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
import { useMutation } from 'convex/react';
import { ConvexError } from 'convex/values';
import { useState } from 'react';
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { z } from 'zod';

// 3. Internal UI components (grouped by type)
import { ButtonLoader } from '@/components/loaders';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Card, CardContent, CardDescription, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '@/components/ui/card';

// 4. Convex API and types
import { api } from '@/convex/_generated/api';
import type { Id, Doc } from '@/convex/_generated/dataModel';

// 5. Utilities last
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
```

## Key Principles:
- **'use client' directive always first** (for client components)
- **External libraries second** (React, Next.js, Convex, etc.)
- **Internal components third** (UI components grouped by type)
- **Convex API and types fourth** (api, Id, Doc types)
- **Utilities last** (cn, formatters, etc.)

## Grouping Examples:
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Group related imports
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';
import { Card, CardContent } from '@/components/ui/card';

// ❌ Bad - Don't mix import types
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
import { useMutation } from 'convex/react';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';
```

## Import Sorting:
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Alphabetical within groups
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Card, CardContent } from '@/components/ui/card';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';

// ✅ Also good - Multi-line for clarity
import {
  Card,
  CardContent,
  CardDescription,
  CardHeader,
  CardTitle
} from '@/components/ui/card';
```